The 2024 Kentucky Democratic presidential primary was held on May 21, 2024, as part of the Democratic Party primaries for the 2024 presidential election. 59 delegates to the Democratic National Convention will be allocated to presidential candidates. Incumbent President Joe Biden won the primary. Uncommitted received  17.9% of the vote and 8 delegates. Biden won a plurality of the vote in all counties except Ballard, Breathitt, Floyd, Knott, Robertson, Union, and Wolfe Counties, which were won by uncommitted.
Candidates
The following candidates have been certified to appear on the ballot in Kentucky:
* Joe Biden
* Dean Phillips (withdrawn)
* Marianne Williamson
* Uncommitted
Additionally, a ballot option for uncommitted delegates was included.
